China arrests 32 for producing, selling illegal cooking oil
2011-09-13 02:16:23 GMT
BEIJING, Sept. 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police have arrested 32 suspects for producing and selling illegal cooking oil in a cross-province crackdown, the Ministry of Public Security said in a statement Tuesday.More than 100 tonnes of such oil, made from leftovers dredged from gutters behind restaurants, were also seized after busting a criminal network spanning 14 provinces, the ministry said.
